92172_-p-1080.jpeg 1080w, https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6721f6603ca1e674e1539dfb/697b5214986ac2465cde9919_AdobeStock_1570392172_-p-1600.jpeg 1600w, https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6721f6603ca1e674e1539dfb/697b5214986ac2465cde9919_AdobeStock_1570392172_-p-2000.jpeg 2000w, https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6721f6603ca1e674e1539dfb/697b5214986ac2465cde9919_AdobeStock_1570392172_-p-2600.jpeg 2600w, https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6721f6603ca1e674e1539dfb/697b5214986ac2465cde9919_AdobeStock_1570392172_-p-3200.jpeg 3200w, https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6721f6603ca1e674e1539dfb/697b5214986ac2465cde9919_AdobeStock_1570392172_.jpeg 3840w\" class=\"post-image\" width=\"1080\" height=\"608\"></div><div class=\"fade-in-blur-on-scroll\" style=\"opacity: 0; filter: blur(6px); transform: translate3d(0px, 25px, 0px) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0deg) rotateY(0deg) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0deg, 0deg); transform-style: preserve-3d;\"><div class=\"section-title padding-bottom padding-top\"><img src=\"https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6721f6603ca1e674e1539db4/67220ffe36d9614e9fc0dc64_Vectors-Wrapper.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1554\" height=\"2\" alt=\"\" class=\"vectors-wrapper\"><div class=\"columns-divider\"><div class=\"author-box-article\"><h3 class=\"title---small no-padding-top\"><span class=\"title---small news no-padding-top\">Fremtidens kapital</span></h3></div><div class=\"tag-column\"><div class=\"tag-solid\"><div class=\"category-text text---small white\">Podcast</div></div><div class=\"tag-outlined\"><div class=\"text---small blue\">January 29, 2026</div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"fade-in-blur-on-scroll\" style=\"opacity: 0; filter: blur(6px); transform: translate3d(0px, 25px, 0px) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0deg) rotateY(0deg) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0deg, 0deg); transform-style: preserve-3d;\"><div class=\"rich-text-container\" style=\"opacity: 0; transform: translate3d(0px, 25px, 0px) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0deg) rotateY(0deg) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0deg, 0deg); transform-style: preserve-3d;\"><div class=\"rich-text w-richtext\"><p>Hvad er kvanteteknologi? Og hvorfor dukker det op i debatter om innovation, national konkurrenceevne og langsigtede investeringer? I denne episode afmystificerer vi, hvad kvantefysik egentlig er, hvorfor den adskiller sig fundamentalt fra klassisk fysik, og hvordan de s\u00e6rlige principper bag kvanteteknologi nu baner vej for helt nye l\u00f8sninger.</p><p>Sammen med kvantefysikerne Kurt Stokbro og Helmut Katzgraber dykker vi ned i aktuelle og kommende anvendelser \u2013 fra kvantekommunikation og -sensorer til kvantecomputere. Vi ser n\u00e6rmere p\u00e5, hvilket potentiale teknologien rummer for virksomheder, produkter og vores samfund, og hvorfor det netop nu er strategisk vigtigt at forst\u00e5 og investere i kvanteomr\u00e5det.</p><p>Thomas Weisbjerg (Partner, Mazanti-Andersen) taler med Helmut Katzgraber (Chief Science Officer &amp; Managing Partner, 55 North) og Kurt Stokbro (CEO, Sparrow Quantum).</p><p>______</p><p>What is quantum technology? And why is it showing up in conversations about innovation, national competitiveness, and long-term investments? In this episode, we demystify what quantum physics is, why it differs fundamentally from classical physics, and how the unique principles behind quantum technology are now paving the way for entirely new solutions.</p><p>Together with quantum physicists Kurt Stokbro and Helmut Katzgraber, we explore current and emerging applications, from quantum communication and sensors to quantum computers. We take a closer look at the potential this technology holds for businesses, products, and our society, and why it is strategically important to understand and invest in the quantum field right now.</p><p>Thomas Weisbjerg (Partner, Mazanti-Andersen) is joined by Kurt Stokbro (CEO, Sparrow Quantum) and Helmut Katzgraber (Chief Science Officer &amp; Managing Partner, 55 North).</p><p>Listen to the episode <a href=\"https://https-podcasts-apple-com-dk-podcast-bag-om-kvanteteknologi-quantum-technology-unpacked-id1854212773-i-1000747164948-l-da\">here</a>.</p></div><div class=\"cloudvideo w-embed\"><div style=\"position: relative; padding-top: 56.25%;\">\n  <iframe src=\"https://customer-en35ajhfwobal3lg.cloudflarestream.com/542b614ea0e3127b9739f23e89e6799d/iframe?muted=true&amp;poster=https%3A%2F%2Fcustomer-en35ajhfwobal3lg.cloudflarestream.com%2F542b614ea0e3127b9739f23e89e6799d%2Fthumbnails%2Fthumbnail.jpg%3Ftime%3D%26height%3D600\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"border: none; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; height: 100%; width: 100%;\" allow=\"accelerometer; gyroscope; autoplay; encrypted-media; picture-in-picture;\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></iframe>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"rich-text-container\" style=\"opacity: 0; transform: translate3d(0px, 25px, 0px) scale3d(1, 1, 1) rotateX(0deg) rotateY(0deg) rotateZ(0deg) skew(0deg, 0deg); transform-style: preserve-3d;\"><div class=\"column-article-facts\"><div class=\"info-5\"><div class=\"tag-column\"><div class=\"tag-solid\"><div class=\"category-text text---small white\">Podcast</div></div><div class=\"tag-outlined\"><div class=\"text---small blue\">January 29, 2026</div></div></div><div class=\"facts-textbox\"><div class=\"facts-text\"><div><div><span class=\"title---small grey\">Investment from the Innovation Fund Denmark:\n</span><span class=\"title---small\">16.2 million kroner.\n</span></div></div></div><div class=\"facts-text\"><div class=\"title---small\"><div><span class=\"title---small grey\">Duration:\n</span><span class=\"title---small\">5 years.\n</span></div></div></div><div class=\"facts-text\"><div><div><span class=\"title---small grey\">Official title:\n</span><span class=\"title---small\">FTQP \u2013 \u2018Fault-Tolerant Architectures for Quantum Computing with Photon Emitters\u2019.\n</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"container\"></div></div><div class=\"section grey\"><div class=\"container